snippet: Gezi Park remains occupied by defiant protesters who on Friday mostly disavowed a compromise between their self-declared leaders and Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
abstract: Istanbul's Gezi Park remains occupied by defiant Turkish protesters who mostly disavowed compromise between their self-declared leaders and Turkey's Prime Min Recep Tayyip Erdogan to end political crisis.

byline.original: By CEYLAN YEGINSU and TIM ARANGO

lead_paragraph: Gezi Park remains occupied by defiant protesters who on Friday mostly disavowed a compromise between their self-declared leaders and Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan.

headline.main: Some Protesters in Turkey Disavow Agreement With Premier to End Park Sit-In
headline.print_headline: Some Protesters in Turkey Disavow Agreement With Premier to End Park Sit-In
